We got a CI.
some old guy close to Tommy.

482
00:22:19.546 --> 00:22:20.839
but nothing concrete yet.

483
00:22:22.799 --> 00:22:25.552
-What's his name?
-Confidential informant.

484
00:22:26.887 --> 00:22:30.307
It's Saxe's contact. and he's
playing it close to the vest.

485
00:22:34.311 --> 00:22:36.063
So are you gonna
call D.C. or what?

486
00:22:43.653 --> 00:22:45.238
[keypad beeps]

487
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:47.949
We got good news. Tash.

488
00:22:48.700 --> 00:22:51.620
Angela got us surveillance
of Dre and Ray Ray
in the street together.

489
00:22:51.703 --> 00:22:53.163
which means they're
officially linked.

490
00:22:54.956 --> 00:22:55.957
Great.

491
00:22:57.084 --> 00:22:59.044
So I just got to get her
a few more details

492
00:22:59.127 --> 00:23:00.504
so she can make her full case.

493
00:23:00.587 --> 00:23:03.090
and me and Tommy
take care of Dre.

494
00:23:03.590 --> 00:23:04.841
[inhales]

495
00:23:05.467 --> 00:23:07.677
Would it be better
to maybe frame somebody

496
00:23:07.761 --> 00:23:09.221
with a lower profile?

497
00:23:09.304 --> 00:23:10.889
Dre's profile
ain't as high as he acts.

498
00:23:12.349 --> 00:23:14.601
I mean. somebody who's
completely off the radar.

499
00:23:14.684 --> 00:23:17.062
No family. no friends. no job.

500
00:23:17.729 --> 00:23:19.523
Somebody nobody would miss.

501
00:23:20.148 --> 00:23:23.151
Sure. but I don't know
anybody else in Ray Ray's crew.

502
00:23:25.570 --> 00:23:26.780
What about Kanan?

503
00:23:31.827 --> 00:23:34.704
[scoffs] Kanan saved our son.

504
00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:36.998
Dre put him in harm's way.

505
00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:39.042
See. you don't
want to target Kanan.

506
00:23:39.126 --> 00:23:40.669
because it would mean
you would have to admit

507
00:23:40.752 --> 00:23:43.171
that everything
that's happened is your fault.

508
00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:46.133
The shooting at Truth.
Killing Rolla.

509
00:23:46.216 --> 00:23:48.927
Everything about Tariq.
Raina's death.

510
00:23:49.511 --> 00:23:50.846
It's your fault.

511
00:23:51.972 --> 00:23:53.140
It's Dre.

512
00:23:58.061 --> 00:24:00.313
What if your plan
goes wrong. Ghost?

513
00:24:01.898 --> 00:24:03.400
[laughter]

514
00:24:07.154 --> 00:24:08.822
Tonight. oh. my God.

515
00:24:08.905 --> 00:24:10.073
[both moan]

516
00:24:10.157 --> 00:24:11.658
All right. all right.

517
00:24:12.993 --> 00:24:15.162
-Tommy. Tommy.
-Why stop?

518
00:24:16.246 --> 00:24:18.331
-Tonight meant so much to me.
-Yeah?

519
00:24:18.582 --> 00:24:19.624
Yes.

520
00:24:20.584 --> 00:24:22.294
They weren't too tough on you?

521
00:24:22.919 --> 00:24:24.588
You know. sometimes. old folks.

522
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:26.506
they got a certain way
of looking at things.

523
00:24:26.590 --> 00:24:28.049
No. I can handle it.

524
00:24:28.466 --> 00:24:29.676
[laughs]

525
00:24:30.427 --> 00:24:33.180
And you stuck up for me.

526
00:24:34.598 --> 00:24:35.765
That's what matters.

527
00:24:38.476 --> 00:24:39.519
[knocking]

528
00:24:40.437 --> 00:24:41.730
What the fuck?

529
00:24:45.108 --> 00:24:46.860
Who you got coming over
this late at night?

530
00:24:46.943 --> 00:24:49.362
Tommy. ain't no nigga
coming over here.

531
00:24:49.446 --> 00:24:50.989
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

532
00:24:51.239 --> 00:24:53.575
-Let me answer the door.
-Go ahead.

533
00:24:53.909 --> 00:24:55.327
Answer the door.

534
00:25:00.874 --> 00:25:01.875
Fuck you want?

535
00:25:02.334 --> 00:25:04.628
-Is LaKeisha Grant here?
-Who wants to know?

536
00:25:04.961 --> 00:25:07.214
Yes. I'm here.

537
00:25:07.797 --> 00:25:10.300
-You've been served.
-Wait. come here.

538
00:25:11.259 --> 00:25:13.011
Better run. motherfucker.

539
00:25:17.807 --> 00:25:20.727
[tense music]

540
00:25:20.810 --> 00:25:22.854
-What the fuck?
-What is it?

541
00:25:23.980 --> 00:25:27.275
A subpoena to appear
in front of a grand jury?

542
00:25:28.485 --> 00:25:29.569
For what?

543
00:25:30.111 --> 00:25:33.323
For the murder
of Raymond Jones. NYPD.

544
00:25:35.825 --> 00:25:38.536
Tommy. is this about
Tasha's alibi?

545
00:25:39.287 --> 00:25:41.414
The one she wanted me to give
for her and Tariq?

546
00:25:43.416 --> 00:25:45.252
Yo. you said
it wouldn't come to this.

547
00:25:45.460 --> 00:25:46.586
I know.

548
00:25:48.463 --> 00:25:50.590
And when I said that.
I thought it wouldn't.

549
00:25:51.007 --> 00:25:52.384
So what am I supposed to do?

550
00:25:54.469 --> 00:25:56.304
Lying to the police
is one thing.

551
00:25:56.388 --> 00:25:59.015
but lying in a courtroom.
under oath?

552
00:25:59.557 --> 00:26:01.518
Yo. they could
send you to jail for that.

553
00:26:02.727 --> 00:26:04.187
You gave Tasha your word.

554
00:26:06.273 --> 00:26:07.899
So that's what this is about.

555
00:26:10.360 --> 00:26:12.153
You coming back into my life.

556
00:26:13.905 --> 00:26:16.241
No. No way.

557
00:26:17.200 --> 00:26:18.702
You know better than that.

558
00:26:19.452 --> 00:26:21.579
I just don't want something bad
happening to the family

559
00:26:21.663 --> 00:26:22.580
because you got scared.

560
00:26:22.664 --> 00:26:23.915
I am scared.

561
00:26:24.666 --> 00:26:26.376
And I got
a goddamn right to be.

562
00:26:26.459 --> 00:26:27.961
I know. and it's fucked up.

563
00:26:29.045 --> 00:26:31.840
But I'll tell you this.
Tasha is smart. talk to her.

564
00:26:32.215 --> 00:26:33.675
If we're gonna
get out of this thing.

565
00:26:33.758 --> 00:26:35.385
you got to do what she says.

566
00:26:37.595 --> 00:26:41.141
And then. we ain't fucking
with her or Ghost anymore.

567
00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:44.978
[exhales]

568
00:26:51.818 --> 00:26:52.986
[knocking]

569
00:26:58.450 --> 00:27:00.201
[Ghost] Hey. son.
I got a question for you.

570
00:27:00.452 --> 00:27:02.120
When you were running
with Kanan.

571
00:27:02.203 --> 00:27:04.205
you ever see Dre
and Ray Ray together?

572
00:27:04.873 --> 00:27:07.042
Yep. in your friend
Breeze's apartment.

573
00:27:07.125 --> 00:27:07.959
where you killed him.

574
00:27:09.502 --> 00:27:10.628
Did Kanan tell you that?

575
00:27:13.840 --> 00:27:15.884
You killed
your own friend. Breeze.

576
00:27:16.634 --> 00:27:19.471
For some territory?
To get ahead in the game?

577
00:27:20.055 --> 00:27:21.348
Breeze was a bad dude.

578
00:27:21.973 --> 00:27:23.391
He was gonna
get us all killed.

579
00:27:24.142 --> 00:27:26.436
You come here
asking me about Kanan. why?

580
00:27:27.354 --> 00:27:28.646
You want to frame him again?

581
00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:31.399
Tariq. I do what I need
to do to solve problems.

582
00:27:32.150 --> 00:27:35.236
I'm not framing Kanan to solve
this one. I promise you that.

583
00:27:36.571 --> 00:27:39.240
You're going to frame Dre.
How though?

584
00:27:39.532 --> 00:27:41.326
He wasn't there. how are you
going to prove he was there?

585
00:27:41.910 --> 00:27:43.578
And then what if
that doesn't work?

586
00:27:43.661 --> 00:27:45.497
-Then Mom goes to jail?
-No. if that doesn't work.

587
00:27:45.580 --> 00:27:47.082
then I turn myself in
for Ray Ray.

588
00:27:47.165 --> 00:27:48.333
Not your mother.
I'm your father.

589
00:27:48.416 --> 00:27:49.793
and your life
is my responsibility.

590
00:27:49.876 --> 00:27:52.087
Yeah. right. you'll just
find another way out.

591
00:27:53.296 --> 00:27:55.590
[soft music]

592
00:27:58.802 --> 00:28:00.303
You're my son. all right?

593
00:28:00.887 --> 00:28:03.139
And what that means is
I would do anything for you.

594
00:28:03.223 --> 00:28:04.808
Including sacrificing my life

595
00:28:04.891 --> 00:28:06.601
to give you the future
I think you deserve.

596
00:28:07.143 --> 00:28:09.771
You don't have to believe it.
but it's true.

597
00:28:11.773 --> 00:28:13.733
So you're going to jail.
not Ma?

598
00:28:14.609 --> 00:28:16.945
Tariq. no one in this family is
going to jail if I can help it.

599
00:28:17.028 --> 00:28:20.323
but yes.
I'll take the rap. not Ma.

600
00:28:20.782 --> 00:28:23.701
[soft music]

601
00:28:35.088 --> 00:28:36.089
Tariq.

602
00:28:36.881 --> 00:28:38.133
We need to talk.

603
00:28:39.050 --> 00:28:41.553
20. 40. 60. 80. 100.

604
00:28:41.636 --> 00:28:43.263
Yeah. yeah.
I know how much it was.

605
00:28:43.346 --> 00:28:45.515
How the fuck
did you make that shot?

606
00:28:45.598 --> 00:28:47.016
[laughs]

607
00:28:47.100 --> 00:28:48.643
Yo. your game is on today.

608
00:28:49.102 --> 00:28:50.854
I've been thinking
about this shit.

609
00:28:50.937 --> 00:28:52.480
How did you and Ghost
get close enough

610
00:28:52.564 --> 00:28:54.816
to Diego Jimenez
to pull that trigger?

611
00:28:55.442 --> 00:28:58.153
From what I can come up with.
Dre wanted Diego dead.

612
00:28:58.611 --> 00:29:01.156
-Ghost made a deal.
-With Dre?

613
00:29:01.906 --> 00:29:03.199
Why the fuck would he do that?

614
00:29:03.324 --> 00:29:04.743
Why is not the question.

615
00:29:04.826 --> 00:29:06.077
What you should
be asking yourself is.

616
00:29:06.161 --> 00:29:07.996
what's Dre's side of the deal?

617
00:29:08.079 --> 00:29:11.374
Who's supposed to get dead?
Me. you?

618
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:12.625
[door opens]

619
00:29:13.752 --> 00:29:14.753
[door closes]

620
00:29:14.836 --> 00:29:16.921
-What up. fellas?
-What's up. Ghost?

621
00:29:17.046 --> 00:29:18.506
Tommy. I need to rap
with you for a minute.

622
00:29:18.590 --> 00:29:20.008
K. you mind
if we have the room?

623
00:29:20.091 --> 00:29:21.176
You always send
a motherfucker

624
00:29:21.259 --> 00:29:23.052
out the room
like a goddamn kid.

625
00:29:23.136 --> 00:29:25.096
Like you forget who taught you
the game in the first place.

626
00:29:25.180 --> 00:29:26.890
Yo. K. you ain't got to go.

627
00:29:27.432 --> 00:29:28.600
I was headed out anyway.

628
00:29:31.811 --> 00:29:33.062
Y'all play nice.

629
00:29:36.524 --> 00:29:37.609
Later. K.

630
00:29:38.610 --> 00:29:41.154
Did you know that LaKeisha
got a subpoena

631
00:29:41.237 --> 00:29:42.781
to appear
in front of a grand jury?

632
00:29:42.864 --> 00:29:45.533
-Shit.
-You're goddamn right. shit.

633
00:29:45.617 --> 00:29:48.244
She got to go under oath.
and lie about

634
00:29:48.328 --> 00:29:51.080
where 'Riq and Tasha were
the night Ray Ray got shot.

635
00:29:51.498 --> 00:29:52.874
I think I got a plan. Tommy.

636
00:29:52.957 --> 00:29:54.626
It'll keep 'Keisha
and all of us safe.

637
00:29:54.709 --> 00:29:55.960
Yeah. why don't that
make me feel better?

638
00:29:56.044 --> 00:29:57.253
Look. when I was on the inside.

639
00:29:57.337 --> 00:29:59.005
was Dre running product
through Truth?

640
00:29:59.088 --> 00:30:00.632
Because I did the books. Tommy.

641
00:30:00.715 --> 00:30:02.008
He made too much money
in there.

642
00:30:02.967 --> 00:30:04.969
-Yeah. that's how we did it.
-We?

643
00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:06.805
And you got an issue
with me keeping secrets?

644
00:30:06.888 --> 00:30:08.181
Come on. Tommy.
do you understand

645
00:30:08.264 --> 00:30:09.516
how much you put at risk
by doing that?

646
00:30:09.599 --> 00:30:11.518
Yeah. I do. my life.

647
00:30:11.810 --> 00:30:14.020
Milan kept us in it.
Petar said keep going.

648
00:30:14.103 --> 00:30:15.855
-I didn't have a choice.
-Okay. Tommy.

649
00:30:15.939 --> 00:30:17.607
I'll just use that.
all right?

650
00:30:17.690 --> 00:30:20.276
I'll say I fired Dre for
running drugs through the club.

651
00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:21.945
Then he reached out
to his contact. Ray Ray.

652
00:30:22.028 --> 00:30:23.071
to get revenge on me.

653
00:30:23.738 --> 00:30:24.989
Of course.
we've got to make sure

654
00:30:25.073 --> 00:30:26.825
that we keep his drug dealing
separate from ours.

655
00:30:26.908 --> 00:30:27.951
Then when we kill that nigga.

656
00:30:28.034 --> 00:30:29.577
we just drop
a La Arana card on him.

657
00:30:29.661 --> 00:30:31.037
Yo. I got one better.

658
00:30:31.496 --> 00:30:33.331
We still got
Diego's head. right?

659
00:30:33.832 --> 00:30:36.251
We drop that shit
in Dre's place.

660
00:30:36.501 --> 00:30:38.086
that gives
the Jimenez motive.

661
00:30:38.878 --> 00:30:40.338
That's better.
and then we drop

662
00:30:40.421 --> 00:30:41.714
the murder weapon on him. too.

663
00:30:41.798 --> 00:30:43.424
Wait. what the fuck
murder weapon?

664
00:30:43.508 --> 00:30:44.676
Tasha said she
got rid of the gun.

665
00:30:44.759 --> 00:30:46.386
She told me the same shit. I'll explain later. all right?

666
00:30:50.306 --> 00:30:52.058
I ain't usually
ride dirty like this.

667
00:30:52.141 --> 00:30:54.602
not since I got caught.
thanks to your mom and pop.

668
00:30:54.978 --> 00:30:56.813
I'm a little short
on manpower these days.

669
00:30:56.980 --> 00:30:58.273
Pfft. don't worry about it.

670
00:30:58.356 --> 00:30:59.941
Ghost gonna
get his time sooner or later.

671
00:31:00.024 --> 00:31:01.192
You going to fuck Ghost up?

672
00:31:01.776 --> 00:31:04.112
No. Ghost going
to fuck himself up.

673
00:31:04.612 --> 00:31:06.406
He thinking about
taking the rap for me

674
00:31:06.489 --> 00:31:08.825
-on this whole Ray Ray shit.
-[laughs]

675
00:31:08.908 --> 00:31:11.411
I ain't never know Ghost to
roll over like no little bitch.

676
00:31:11.494 --> 00:31:13.329
Motherfucker win.
no matter what.

677
00:31:13.830 --> 00:31:15.707
You don't believe
that shit. though. right?

678
00:31:15.790 --> 00:31:18.668
I mean. I don't know.
He seemed real enough about it.

679
00:31:19.502 --> 00:31:22.088
I think he might try to
pin all of it on Dre first.

680
00:31:22.171 --> 00:31:25.842
Now. that do sound like Ghost.
Maybe you can trust that nigga.

681
00:31:26.217 --> 00:31:27.510
Close the trunk.

682
00:31:27.635 --> 00:31:29.304
Let's take this shit
to the "Eye-talians."

683
00:31:29.387 --> 00:31:31.180
and then I want
to show you something.

684
00:31:33.933 --> 00:31:36.269
[tense music]

685
00:31:52.160 --> 00:31:54.245
Don't you already
have everything you wanted?

686
00:31:55.079 --> 00:31:56.998
Relax. I'm gonna
do you a favor.

687
00:31:57.081 --> 00:31:58.917
Oh. you're gonna
do me a favor. really?

688
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:00.335
After blackmailing me?

689
00:32:00.877 --> 00:32:02.545
That just means
we're on the same side.

690
00:32:03.463 --> 00:32:06.382
My advice is that you distance
yourself from Andre.

691
00:32:07.216 --> 00:32:09.844
If you don't.
you won't win the election.

692
00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:13.723
I'm going to need more than
your word. and your spite.

693
00:32:20.855 --> 00:32:21.981
Here's the truth.

694
00:32:23.024 --> 00:32:24.275
I fired Andre.

695
00:32:25.234 --> 00:32:27.570
Because while I was
wrongfully imprisoned.

696
00:32:27.654 --> 00:32:30.114
I suspected he was pushing
drugs through this club.

697
00:32:30.657 --> 00:32:33.785
I was right. and ever since.
your friend. Andre.

698
00:32:33.868 --> 00:32:35.536
has had a vendetta against me.

699
00:32:36.412 --> 00:32:38.206
Why are you
telling me this shit now?

700
00:32:38.289 --> 00:32:39.582
Because he's pulling
the same tricks

701
00:32:39.666 --> 00:32:41.042
with the Basset Hotel Group.

702
00:32:41.125 --> 00:32:43.002
I can tell because
of how much money they've made

703
00:32:43.086 --> 00:32:44.796
in such a short amount of time.

704
00:32:44.879 --> 00:32:46.506
He's in with some bad people.

705
00:32:46.923 --> 00:32:49.133
and it's going to come down
on him real soon.

706
00:32:49.217 --> 00:32:51.469
which means that if you don't
break ties with him.

707
00:32:51.552 --> 00:32:53.429
he's gonna drag you
to the bottom.

708
00:32:55.348 --> 00:32:56.724
What about you. James?

709
00:32:58.601 --> 00:33:00.061
You stick close to me.

710
00:33:00.812 --> 00:33:03.272
And I'll be pulling you up
with me to the top.

711
00:33:08.736 --> 00:33:11.656
Back in the day.
me. Tommy. and your pops
used to run this block.

712
00:33:12.073 --> 00:33:14.242
We was around your age.
we was selling crack

713
00:33:14.325 --> 00:33:16.202
a hundred miles an hour
up the street.

714
00:33:16.536 --> 00:33:18.538
Until the cops
started to know our faces.

715
00:33:19.288 --> 00:33:21.124
Every time they seen us.
they used to hop out.

716
00:33:21.207 --> 00:33:22.333
run down on us.

717
00:33:23.376 --> 00:33:26.004
Ghost would be gone
before we could even think
to run and shit.

718
00:33:27.964 --> 00:33:30.133
See. he-he ain't try
to outrun the cops.

719
00:33:30.883 --> 00:33:34.220
He just figured that as long as
he could outrun me and Tommy.

720
00:33:34.303 --> 00:33:35.430
the cops would settle for us.

721
00:33:36.014 --> 00:33:38.433
[scoffs] Nigga always
thinking about himself.

722
00:33:40.101 --> 00:33:41.602
Well. it's worked
for him so far.

723
00:33:45.690 --> 00:33:48.568
Take these dimes.
hit me when you get them off.

724
00:33:49.027 --> 00:33:50.069
When I get them off?

725
00:33:50.778 --> 00:33:52.405
How the fuck
I'm supposed to do that?

726
00:33:52.488 --> 00:33:54.407
-I don't know these people.
-Figure it out.

727
00:33:54.490 --> 00:33:55.658
Don't come back until you do.

728
00:33:56.951 --> 00:33:58.161
Just don't get caught.

729
00:33:58.745 --> 00:33:59.746
All right.

730
00:34:06.753 --> 00:34:08.963
-Hey.
-Congratulations.

731
00:34:09.881 --> 00:34:11.090
